spec: socket_extra163
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra162.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__repr__/__str__/__enter__/__exit__ qualname strings and lengths / function vs wrapper_descriptor types (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra161.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.send/__recv/__sendto/__recvfrom qualname strings and lengths / all four are method_descriptor (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra156.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') / socket.__spec__.name.__eq__('socket') / socket.socket method qualnames (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra162."
    - "Wave 345 theme: socket module __spec__ origin and submodule_search_locations attributes — socket.__spec__.origin.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') / socket.__spec__.origin.__contains__('socket') / socket.__spec__.submodule_search_locations.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') / socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') (confirmed) / socket.__spec__.name.__eq__('socket') (confirmed). socket_extra156 anchors __class__.__name__ and name; this spec anchors origin type and content checks and the submodule_search_locations attribute as the primary novel content."
    - "socket.__spec__.origin.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.origin.__contains__('socket') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.submodule_search_locations is None (NoneType). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__ == 'ModuleSpec'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.name == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.name.__len__() == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__len__() == 10. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.__spec__.origin is the filesystem path to socket.py. The actual path is platform-specific and must not be hardcoded in the spec. We verify: (1) origin.__class__.__name__ == 'str' (the origin is a string), and (2) origin.__contains__('socket') == True (the path contains the module name 'socket'). This approach tests the structural property without embedding a machine-specific path."
    - "Note: socket.__spec__.submodule_search_locations is None (NoneType). socket is a plain module (not a package). The socket module (Lib/socket.py) is a single file, not a directory package. Packages have non-None submodule_search_locations. We check via __class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') since None cannot be used directly as an expected value in python_call_eq specs."
    - "Note: socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__ == 'ModuleSpec' (10 chars). socket_extra156 anchors this as a table row; confirmed here alongside origin checks. socket.__spec__.name == 'socket' (6 chars). Both 'socket' (module name) and 'struct' (struct module name) have 6-char names; both are plain non-package modules with None submodule_search_locations."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

